%I A394563 #17 Apr 10 2026 00:46:55
%S A394563 1,2,5,7,17
%N A394563 Least integer a(n) such that every graph on a(n) vertices has an induced regular subgraph of order at least n.
%C A394563 a(6)>=21 and a(7)>=30.
%H A394563 Paul W. Dyson and Brendan D. McKay, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2604.08215">Ramsey numbers for regular induced subgraphs</a>, arXiv:2604.08215 [math.CO] (2026).
%H A394563 Paul Dyson and Brendan McKay, <a href="https://users.cecs.anu.edu.au/~bdm/data/ramsey.html">Ramsey Graphs</a> (section Regular induced subgraphs)
%H A394563 S. Fajtlowicz, T. McColgan, T. Read, and W. Staton, <a href="https://combinatorialpress.com/article/ars/Volume%20039/volume-39-paper-15.pdf">Ramsey numbers for induced regular subgraphs</a>, Ars Combinatoria, 39 (1995) 149-154.
%e A394563 a(3)=5 because the path on 4 vertices has no induced regular subgraph of order more than 2, whereas every graph with 5 vertices either has one of order 3 or 5.
%Y A394563 Cf. A390257, A394564, A394574.
%K A394563 nonn,hard,more
%O A394563 1,2
%A A394563 _Brendan McKay_, Mar 24 2026
